# Rust
/target
**/target/
Cargo.lock
Cargo.lock.bak
Cargo.lock.new

# Cargo local-dev overrides — never tracked; sibling-checkout patches
# already live in the workspace root Cargo.toml [patch] block.
.cargo/config.toml
.cargo/config.toml.disabled

# Python wheel build artifacts
empyrean-py/dist/
empyrean-py/build/
empyrean-py/*.egg-info/
empyrean-py/.venv/
empyrean-py/uv.lock
# maturin develop drops the compiled extension module into the package
# dir so `import empyrean` resolves it; that .so is build output, not
# source. Each rebuild churns bytes — keep it out of commits.
empyrean-py/python/empyrean/_empyrean_rs*.so
empyrean-py/python/empyrean/_empyrean_rs*.pyd
# The closed-source engine, copied next to the extension by the release
# workflow so it ships inside the wheel (found at run time via dladdr).
# Build output, never committed.
empyrean-py/python/empyrean/libempyrean.dylib
empyrean-py/python/empyrean/libempyrean.so

# Validation C-runner binary — compiled artifact of
# `make -C validation/runners/c`, not source.
validation/runners/c/runner

# Notebook scratch
**/.ipynb_checkpoints/
empyrean-py/test.ipynb
empyrean-py/*.ipynb
notebooks/

# Local dev / notebook helper scripts — personal workflow, not part
# of the wheel build. Keep on disk for the developer who wrote them
# (rebuilding empyrean-py against a notebook session is faster than
# every contributor re-deriving the steps), but don't track in main.
empyrean-py/build-dev-env.sh
empyrean-py/launch-notebook.sh

# Sphinx / mkdocs build output
empyrean-py/docs/_build/
empyrean-py/docs/_generated/

# empyrean-py test validation data — fetched fresh in CI from villeneuve
# (the "Fetch validation data from villeneuve" job step populates the dir).
# Locally this is a developer symlink to the sibling villeneuve checkout,
# whose target is an absolute machine-local path; tracking it makes CI's
# `mkdir -p tests/data` fail (the path already exists as a dangling symlink).
empyrean-py/tests/data

# Validation run outputs (regenerated by `make all` in empyrean-validation)
results/

# ADES observation fixtures for the validation catalog — the per-object
# `.psv` files churn over time as observations are added / debiased /
# re-fetched. Carry them out-of-band rather than tracking in git.
validation/fixtures/psv/

# Code parking lot — historical FFI salvage; not a workspace member, not built.
empyrean-cli/ffi-salvage/

# OS junk
.DS_Store

# Python bytecode
**/*.pyc
**/__pycache__/

# pytest / coverage
.pytest_cache/
.coverage
htmlcov/

# Editor / IDE
.idea/
.vscode/
*.swp

# Claude Code session artifacts (agent memory, scratch, transcripts)
.claude/
